  "body": "Is this a bug report or feature request?\r\n<!-- Remove only one -->\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Bug Report**\r\n\r\nWhat happened: When deploying Rook via Helm charts and then attempting to remove a node later on by editing the cluster CRD, the operator does not have the required permissions to do so.  This error is found in the operator log:\r\n```\r\n2018-01-27 14:02:37.774269 E | op-cluster: failed to update cluster in namespace rook. failed to start the osds.\r\n1 failures encountered while running osds in namespace rook:\r\nfailed to update osd replica set for removed node xyz.\r\nreplicasets.extensions \"rook-ceph-osd-xyz\" is forbidden:\r\nUser \"system:serviceaccount:kube-system:rook-operator\" cannot update replicasets.extensions in the namespace \"rook\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nHow to reproduce it (minimal and precise):\r\n<!-- Please let us know any circumstances for reproduction of your bug. -->\r\n1. Deploy Rook operator via a Helm chart\r\n1. Create a Rook cluster with `useAllNodes: false` and an explicit list of nodes\r\n1. Edit the cluster CRD to remove 1 of the nodes",
